600,000 baby salmon will be released into the river.
During the AS Latvenergo fish stock recovery programme, salmon and sea trout hatchlings are being released this week in the Daugava at Mangaļsala, and this year more than 600 000 one-year-old salmon and sea trout hatchlings from the Bior Tomes and Dole fish farms of the scientific institute are planned to be released.
