"The names of the artists are available on the website www.sansusi.lv", says Armands Siliņš.
The splendid group of artists includes, for example, violinist Eva Binder, cellist Kristine Blaumane, opera star Inga Kalna, clarinetist Guntis Kuzma, trumpeter Jānis Porietis, pianist Reinis Zariņš, the Quadra and RIX quartets and even the Estonian aerial acrobat Grete Gross, who together with Latvian musicians Erik Kirchfeld, Martins Zilberts and actress Anca Strazdas created the contemporary circus show Confines about the artist's inner struggle.
New works have also been created especially for the festival.
In the children's play "Insect", composed by Olesja Kozlovska and Jakob Niemannis based on the story by F. Kafka, the entomologist (insect researcher) Uģis Piterāns will participate along with Armandas Siliņš, musicians and actors.
Oskar Herliņš has composed the first String Quartet, while Anna Kirse has written The Opera of Trees, a performance whose main characters, directed by Andras Kalnozol with video projections by Katrin Neiburg and set design by Andras Eglish, will be trees in three small puddles in a three-hectare lime grove.
