It may come as little comfort to Britain that at least one Briton won the gold medal - Fiji's Ben Ryan, former coach of England at Wimbledon.
For Britain, it was an exciting adventure.
Eight years ago, under Ryan, they lost every game in a rugby sevens series in Adelaide.
They only lost one game this time.
Defeat is painful, but growth is surprising.
Fiji began the match with a spectacular display of British strength.
